From: Alp Lab AB
Date: Wed, 3 Jun 2026 20:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] clk: renesas: r9a09g056: keep CM33-owned RSCI7/RIIC8 clocks
 and MSTOP gates on

Copyright (c) 2026 Alp Lab AB
SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0

AMP clock-ownership fix for the ALP E1M V2N SoM: RSCI7 (SCI7 Simple-SPI)
and RIIC8 drive the on-module GD32G553 supervisor MCU from the Cortex-M33
system manager, not from Linux.

The rzv2h-cpg driver couples each module clock to its CPG BUS_MSTOP bits:
disabling the clock also asserts the module-stop, which gates *register
access* to the peripheral.  At late init, clk_disable_unused walks every
module clock with no Linux consumer -- including RSCI7/RIIC8, which Linux
never uses -- turns the clocks off and asserts their MSTOP bits.  The
CM33, mid-operation on SCI7 at that moment, bus-faults on its next
register access and is dead until the next power cycle.  (Verified on
silicon: at the U-Boot prompt all gates are still open exactly as BL2
released them; they close during Linux boot, at the unused-clock sweep.)

The CM33 cannot help itself: it can write its own CPG CLKON view, but the
BUS_MSTOP registers are not writable from the CM33 master, so only the
A55 side can keep the bus gates open.

Mark all five rsci_7_* module clocks and riic_8_ckm DEF_MOD_CRITICAL:

  - CLK_IS_CRITICAL keeps the clocks enabled forever, so the unused-clock
    sweep skips them and never asserts their MSTOP bits;
  - the driver's critical-clock registration path seeds the MSTOP
    refcount, (re-)releasing the gates early in boot;
  - every sharer of BUS_MSTOP(11, BIT(10)) is marked, so the per-bit
    refcount can never drop to zero through a non-critical sibling.

Silicon-validated 2026-06-03 on E1M-V2M101 (RZ/V2N + GD32G553): across
two cold power cycles and a warm reboot, with zero manual intervention,
CLKON_8 keeps bits 0-4 set and BUS11_MSTOP bit 10 released through and
beyond clk_disable_unused (the rest of BUS11 reads stopped, as expected),
and the CM33<->GD32 SPI link runs uninterrupted from ~2 s after power-on.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [board-specific AMP ownership policy; a
DT-driven (e.g. critical-clocks) representation would be the upstreamable
form later]

Signed-off-by: Alp Lab AB
---
 drivers/clk/renesas/r9a09g056-cpg.c | 22 ++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/clk/renesas/r9a09g056-cpg.c b/drivers/clk/renesas/r9a09g056-cpg.c
index ca6129245a4d..64dc9fa692be 100644
--- a/drivers/clk/renesas/r9a09g056-cpg.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/renesas/r9a09g056-cpg.c
@@ -452,15 +452,25 @@ static const struct rzv2h_mod_clk r9a09g056_mod_clks[] __initconst = {
 						BUS_MSTOP(11, BIT(9))),
 	DEF_MOD("rsci_6_ps_ps1_n",		CLK_PLLCLN_DIV64, 7, 15, 3, 31,
 						BUS_MSTOP(11, BIT(9))),
-	DEF_MOD("rsci_7_pclk",			CLK_PLLCM33_DIV16, 8, 0, 4, 0,
+	/*
+	 * ALP E1M-V2M101 AMP clock ownership: RSCI7 (and RIIC8 below) belong to
+	 * the Cortex-M33 system manager, which drives the on-module GD32G553
+	 * supervisor over SCI7 Simple-SPI (and I2C8).  The CM33 cannot release
+	 * the CPG BUS_MSTOP gates itself, so if Linux disables these unused-
+	 * by-Linux clocks (clk_disable_unused), the coupled MSTOP assertion
+	 * bus-faults the CM33 mid-operation.  CRITICAL keeps clock + MSTOP
+	 * held for the remote core.  All sharers of the MSTOP bit are marked
+	 * so the refcount can never drop to zero.
+	 */
+	DEF_MOD_CRITICAL("rsci_7_pclk",			CLK_PLLCM33_DIV16, 8, 0, 4, 0,
 						BUS_MSTOP(11, BIT(10))),
-	DEF_MOD("rsci_7_tclk",			CLK_PLLCM33_DIV16, 8, 1, 4, 1,
+	DEF_MOD_CRITICAL("rsci_7_tclk",			CLK_PLLCM33_DIV16, 8, 1, 4, 1,
 						BUS_MSTOP(11, BIT(10))),
-	DEF_MOD("rsci_7_ps_ps3_n",		CLK_PLLCLN_DIV1024, 8, 2, 4, 2,
+	DEF_MOD_CRITICAL("rsci_7_ps_ps3_n",		CLK_PLLCLN_DIV1024, 8, 2, 4, 2,
 						BUS_MSTOP(11, BIT(10))),
-	DEF_MOD("rsci_7_ps_ps2_n",		CLK_PLLCLN_DIV256, 8, 3, 4, 3,
+	DEF_MOD_CRITICAL("rsci_7_ps_ps2_n",		CLK_PLLCLN_DIV256, 8, 3, 4, 3,
 						BUS_MSTOP(11, BIT(10))),
-	DEF_MOD("rsci_7_ps_ps1_n",		CLK_PLLCLN_DIV64, 8, 4, 4, 4,
+	DEF_MOD_CRITICAL("rsci_7_ps_ps1_n",		CLK_PLLCLN_DIV64, 8, 4, 4, 4,
 						BUS_MSTOP(11, BIT(10))),
 	DEF_MOD("rsci_8_pclk",			CLK_PLLCM33_DIV16, 8, 5, 4, 5,
 						BUS_MSTOP(11, BIT(11))),
@@ -490,7 +500,7 @@ static const struct rzv2h_mod_clk r9a09g056_mod_clks[] __initconst = {
 						BUS_MSTOP(10, BIT(15))),
 	DEF_MOD("i3c_0_tclk",			CLK_PLLCLN_DIV8, 9, 2, 4, 18,
 						BUS_MSTOP(10, BIT(15))),
-	DEF_MOD("riic_8_ckm",			CLK_PLLCM33_DIV16, 9, 3, 4, 19,
+	DEF_MOD_CRITICAL("riic_8_ckm",			CLK_PLLCM33_DIV16, 9, 3, 4, 19,
 						BUS_MSTOP(3, BIT(13))),
 	DEF_MOD("riic_0_ckm",			CLK_PLLCLN_DIV16, 9, 4, 4, 20,
 						BUS_MSTOP(1, BIT(1))),
--
2.43.0
